  "text": "To test whether the 3Ј ORF of RPP14 mRNA was sufficient to complement the yeast dehydratase knockout or point mutations, the corresponding human 3Ј ORF was amplified by polymerase chain reaction (PCR) from the cerebellum cDNA library using the primers Hshtd2yEP352f (5Ј-GCTCTAGAAT-GTTCCCACTAATTTCCAGCCAT-3Ј) and Hshtd2yEP352r (5Ј-CCGCTCGAGTCAGGATTTGGAAGCTTCTGG-3Ј) introducing an XbaI restriction site 5Ј of the initiation ATG and an XhoI restriction site 3Ј of the stop codon, respectively. The digested PCR product was ligated into the S. cerevisiae expression vector pYE352-CTA1 [CITATION_1] , replacing the CTA1 ORF and resulting in plasmid pYE352-Hshtd2. Plasmids pYE352-Hshtd2, pYE352-htd2, and pYE352-Cta1 were transformed into yeast strains htd2-1 and ⌬htd2 on SC-Ura Ϫ with 2% glucose. The transformants were moved to synthetic complete plates with 3% glycerol and grown at 30°C for 6 -7 days.",
